description.plain:
Born in Brooklyn and of Guyanese descent, Carlos St. John Phillips grew up listening to a lot of Caribbean music.  With his father absent, JHN tried his hand at drug dealing but didn’t like it. After this, he followed his older brother into rapping.  He said of the experience, “my older brother felt like a father. He was only two years older than me so that was all I had. Whatever he would’ve done I was going to do.”  In the beginnings of his music career he went by Carlos Saint John. He describes his earlier rapping style as more aggressive and less melodic than his current output. He also used this name for a brief time when he put rapping on hold to spend time writing songs for other artists. JHN has co-writing credits on songs like Usher’s 2016 hits “Crash” and “Rivals.”

He is part of a collective called GØDD COMPLEXx.

songs.full_title: Roses by SAINt JHN
songs.title: Roses

description.plain:
After its release back in 2016, “Roses” quickly gained mainstream popularity, which worked as one of SAINt JHN’s most important components of his rap-career.

The track also worked as his introduction song for new listeners, with him rapping about his type of girl, his background, how he isn’t one to mess with and just his general life.

The track also served as the first single for JHN’s debut studio album “Collection One”.

songs.title: Roses (Imanbek Remix)

description.plain:
A surprise release from SAINt JHN features a remix of his biggest hit to date “Roses”.

The remix started off as an unoffical remix uploaded to YouTube. The video quickly gained attraction and managed to rack up 6+ million views in just 4 months. The song was especially popular in Russia, enough to it reaching the number 1 spot for most Shazamed song in the country. This later lead it on to being placed as number 19 on the global chart.

The remix comes 3 years after the release of the original back in 2016 and features a very high-pitched JHN alongside an EDM-beat, whereas the original had much darker vibe to it.

songs.full_title: Trap by SAINt JHN (Ft. Lil Baby)
songs.title: Trap

description.plain:
“Trap” marks as Lenny’s first song of 2019, and the third single off of his second studio album “Ghetto Lenny’s Love Songs”.
Noteworthy is this also only the second song ever from Lenny, with a feature on it, with the first one being “Lust” featuring Janelle Kroll.

“Trap” is Lenny and Lil Baby showing how they’re both dealing with their newfound fame and wealth after being raised in a tough environment. The pair share a lot of similarities, with them both being raised by a single mother in poverty, then turning to drug dealing at a young age to earn money. Lenny has been verbal on many occasions, that if it wouldn’t have been for rap, he would most likely still be selling drugs, which he even has a song about, titled “Dope Dealer” released through his rap-collective GØDD COMPLEXx.
Same goes for Baby, who never thought that rap was going to be his career. But after being pursued by Quality Control Music’s Pee and Coach K to keep on rapping, kept him out of the drug selling business
